text.section:
Unless the person is under eighteen (18) years of age, in addition to the penalties specified in KRS 189A.010, a person convicted of violation of KRS 189A.010(1)(a), (b), (c), (d), or (e) shall have his or her license to operate a motor vehicle or motorcycle revoked by the court as follows:
For the first offense within a five (5) year period, for a period of not less than thirty (30) days nor more than one hundred twenty (120) days;
For the second offense within a five (5) year period, for a period of not less than twelve (12) months nor more than eighteen (18) months;
For a third offense within a five (5) year period, for a period of not less than twenty-four (24) months nor more than thirty-six (36) months; and
For a fourth or subsequent offense within a five (5) year period, sixty (60) months.
For purposes of this section, "offense" shall have the same meaning as described in KRS 189A.010(5)(e).
